[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m looking into a potential bug with the header matching in `readHttp1Headers`. It seems to work with partial matches but has issues when finalizing. There might also be an upgrade path issue with the string not being URL-encoded. I’m considering if `createHttp2Settings` should be static since it doesn't use an instance, although Checkstyle doesn’t require that. There's also a concern about deprecated APIs with `AbstractHandler`, especially in Jetty versions. Lastly, the new test seems to send GET requests with response bodies, which might need attention for dynamic access.
